{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "toc-hr-collapsed": false
   },
   "source": [
    "Regla delta generalizada y algoritmos con supermemoria\n",
    "===\n",
    "\n",
    "* *30 min* | Ultima modificación: Junio 22, 2019"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Descripción del problema"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En el algoritmo de gradiente descendente, el proceso de optimización usa la siguiente ecuación recursiva:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$ \\mathbf{w}_k = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{f}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1})$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Como caso de aplicación se desea ajustar el modelo de regresión lineal "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$y_i = w_0 + w_1 * x_i$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "al siguiente conjunto de datos:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = [0.1087,  0.2698,  0.3765,  0.2146,  0.9155,  \n",
    "     0.0246,  0.0221,  0.8632,  0.6460,  0.2092,  \n",
    "     0.8567,  0.1591,  0.9647,  0.6231,  0.7460,  \n",
    "     0.3654,  0.3065,  0.6886,  0.4966,  0.2008,  \n",
    "     0.2618,  0.7607,  0.1563,  0.4424,  0.7731]\n",
    "\n",
    "d = [0.9519,  1.1237,  1.2360,  1.0526,  2.0743,\n",
    "     0.7906,  0.7603,  2.0533,  1.6887,  1.0563,\n",
    "     2.0991,  0.8953,  2.1917,  1.6266,  1.8508,\n",
    "     1.2828,  1.2283,  1.8722,  1.4657,  1.0418,\n",
    "     1.1097,  1.7826,  0.9711,  1.4267,  1.8248]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Para ello, se usa como función de pérdida la sumatoria del error cuadrático (SSE) definda como:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$\\text{SSE}(w_0, w_1) = \\sum_i (d_i - w_0 - w_1 x_i)^2 $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#\n",
    "# Sumatoria del error cuadrático o pérdida cuadrática\n",
    "#\n",
    "def SSE(w0, w1):\n",
    "    return (sum( [(v - w0 - w1*u)**2  for u, v in zip(x, d)] ))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Como ya se explicó, la función SSE() es una cuadrática con forma de tazón y un único punto de mínima que corresponde al valor óptimo de los parámetros $w_0$ y $w_1$. La gráfica de la cuadrática es presentada a continuación."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib import cm\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_contour():\n",
    "    #\n",
    "    W0 = np.arange(-0.5, 3.0, 0.05)\n",
    "    W1 = np.arange(-0.5, 3.0, 0.05)\n",
    "    W0, W1 = np.meshgrid(W0, W1)\n",
    "    F = SSE(W0, W1)\n",
    "    #\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
    "    ax.set_aspect('equal', 'box')\n",
    "    ax.contour(W0, W1, F, levels=[0, 1, 2, 3, 5, 10, 20, 40, 60, 90])\n",
    "    ax.grid()\n",
    "    \n",
    "plot_contour()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Tal como ya se habia explicado, la técnica del gradiente descendente se basa en un proceso iterativo que usa la siguiente ecuación para refinar la aproximación al valor óptimo de los parámetros:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$ \\mathbf{w}_k = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1})$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "con:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1}) = \n",
    "\\left[\n",
    "  \\begin{array}{c}\n",
    "  -2 \\sum_i  e_{i,k-1}\n",
    "  \\\\\n",
    "  -2 \\sum_i  e_{i,k-1} x_i\n",
    "  \\end{array}\n",
    "\\right]\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Estos cómputos son implementados a continuación."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#\n",
    "# Gradiente de la función de error (SSE)\n",
    "#\n",
    "def gSSE(w0, w1):\n",
    "    e = [(v - w0 - w1*u)  for u, v in zip(x, d)]\n",
    "    gw0 = -2 * sum(e)\n",
    "    gw1 = -2 * sum([q*v for q, v in zip(e,x)])    \n",
    "    return (gw0, gw1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def mejora(w0, w1, mu):\n",
    "    ## computa el gradiente para los parámetros actuales\n",
    "    gw0, gw1 = gSSE(w0, w1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## realiza la corrección de los parámetros\n",
    "    w0 = w0 - mu * gw0\n",
    "    w1 = w1 - mu * gw1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## retorna los parámetros corregidos\n",
    "    return (w0, w1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "El proceso de optimización se realiza de un punto inicial arbitrario. A continuación se presenta el valor encontrado y la traza de puntos que recorre el algoritmo hasta llegar al óptimo."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Valores encontrados\n",
      "\n",
      "  w0 = 0.675531\n",
      "  w1 = 1.643269\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Punto de inicio\n",
    "w0 = 0.5\n",
    "w1 = 3.0\n",
    "\n",
    "history_w0 = [w0]\n",
    "history_w1 = [w1]\n",
    "history_f  = [SSE(w0, w1)]\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(20):\n",
    "    w0, w1 = mejora(w0, w1, 0.03)\n",
    "    history_w0.append(w0)\n",
    "    history_w1.append(w1)\n",
    "    history_f.append(SSE(w0, w1))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nValores encontrados\\n\\n  w0 = {:f}\\n  w1 = {:f}\\n'.format(w0, w1))    \n",
    "\n",
    "plot_contour()\n",
    "plt.plot(history_w0, history_w1, color='red');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note que el algoritmo realiza una caminata en zigzag (va y se devuelve) intentando llegar al óptimo. Este comportamiento es indeseable y se desea evitar el zigzag ya que se desperdician iteraciones para llegar al óptimo."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Solución"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Para evitar el zigzag, se desea usar la dirección del gradiente actual ponderada por la dirección previa. Esta metodología se conoce como regla delta (en la jerga de redes neuronales artificiales) o gradiente con memoria (en investigación de operaciones). "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Específicamente, el proceso de optimización se basa en la siguiente ecuación recursiva (ya estudiada):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$ \\mathbf{w}_k = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1})$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "la cual que puede ser reescrita como:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$\\mathbf{w}_k = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} + \\Delta \\mathbf{w}_{k-1}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "con:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$\\Delta \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} = - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1})$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "La dirección tomada en la iteración anterior será $\\Delta \\mathbf{w}_{k-2}$. Ahora, solo es necesario agregar este término a la ecuación anterior, ponderado por un parámetro $\\beta$ conocido comúnmente como *momentum*:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$\\Delta \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} = - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1}) + \\beta \\Delta \\mathbf{w}_{k-2}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "La implementación es la siguiente:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def mejora(w0, w1, mu, beta):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Corrección en la iteración anterior.\n",
    "    global previous_delta_w0\n",
    "    global previous_delta_w1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Computó del gradiente para los parámetros actuales\n",
    "    gw0, gw1 = gSSE(w0, w1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Corrección de los parámetros\n",
    "    delta_w0 = - mu * gw0 + beta * previous_delta_w0\n",
    "    delta_w1 = - mu * gw1 + beta * previous_delta_w1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Almacenamiento de la corrección para la siguiente iteración\n",
    "    previous_delta_w0 = delta_w0\n",
    "    previous_delta_w1 = delta_w1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    w0 = w0 + delta_w0\n",
    "    w1 = w1 + delta_w1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # retorna los parámetros corregidos\n",
    "    return (w0, w1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "El proceso de iterativo de optimización es el siguiente:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Valores encontrados\n",
      "\n",
      "  w0 = 0.717213\n",
      "  w1 = 1.535152\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Punto de inicio\n",
    "w0 = 0.5\n",
    "w1 = 3.0\n",
    "\n",
    "history_w0 = [w0]\n",
    "history_w1 = [w1]\n",
    "history_f  = [SSE(w0, w1)]\n",
    "\n",
    "previous_delta_w0 = 0\n",
    "previous_delta_w1 = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(20):\n",
    "    w0, w1 = mejora(w0, w1, 0.01, 0.7)\n",
    "    history_w0.append(w0)\n",
    "    history_w1.append(w1)\n",
    "    history_f.append(SSE(w0, w1))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nValores encontrados\\n\\n  w0 = {:f}\\n  w1 = {:f}\\n'.format(w0, w1))    \n",
    "\n",
    "plot_contour()\n",
    "plt.plot(history_w0, history_w1, color='red');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

   ]
  },

   ]
  }
